### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8082/api/v1
@bookingId = 1

### 1. Crear reserva pública (sin user_id)
POST {{baseUrl}}/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "apartment_id": 15,
  "user_info": {
    "first_name": "Lolo",
    "last_name": "Gala",
    "dni": "4321456",
    "phone": "+5491145654432",
    "email": "lolo@example.com"
  },
  "check_in": "2025-11-25",
  "check_out": "2025-11-30",
  "guests": 2,
  "payment_method": "transferencia"
}

### 2. Crear reserva como admin para un usuario
POST {{baseUrl}}/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "apartment_id": 24,
  "user_id": 1,
  "user_info": {
    "first_name": "Macarena",
    "last_name": "Rodriguez",
    "dni": "40456543",
    "phone": "+5491198765238",
    "email": "macarena@example.com"
  },
  "check_in": "2025-11-30",
  "check_out": "2025-12-05",
  "guests": 3,
  "payment_method": "Tarjeta de crédito"
}

### 3. Obtener reserva por ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/bookings/{{bookingId}}

### 4. Obtener reservas por usuario
GET {{baseUrl}}/bookings/user/1

### 5. Actualizar reserva (cambiar fecha)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/bookings/{{bookingId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "check_in": "2025-11-21",
  "check_out": "2025-11-25"
}

### 6. Cancelar reserva
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/bookings/{{bookingId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "cancelled"
}

### 7. Eliminar reserva
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/bookings/{{bookingId}}

### 8. Crear reserva que fallará por disponibilidad (fechas solapadas)
POST {{baseUrl}}/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "apartment_id": 2,
  "user_info": {
    "first_name": "Pedro",
    "last_name": "Lopez",
    "dni": "11223344",
    "phone": "+5491155566677",
    "email": "pedro@example.com"
  },
  "check_in": "2025-11-20",
  "check_out": "2025-11-24",
  "guests": 4,
  "payment_method": "transferencia"
}

